of nominal and cardinal scales. 

33
00:03:24,955 --> 00:03:28,035
What is a coordinate system? 

34
00:03:28,412 --> 00:03:33,592
A coordinate system
it is primarily two axes,...

35
00:03:36,888 --> 00:03:39,528
one origin,...

36
00:03:39,824 --> 00:03:45,784
an orientation of these axes 

37
00:03:45,784 --> 00:03:51,974
and a measurement scale along
these axes.

38
00:03:52,096 --> 00:03:59,976
Our first example here, 
which is called a Cartesian system..

39
00:04:01,572 --> 00:04:04,032
and that defines a plane. 

40
00:04:04,863 --> 00:04:09,123
One can also define a coordinate
system along an axis. 

41
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:16,383
If I take here an example
with an axis of a road

42
00:04:16,383 --> 00:04:28,953
I can also link to this axis, 
a scale, an origin... 

43
00:04:30,075 --> 00:04:36,615
and thus I can find an object
or an event along this axis. 

44
00:04:36,945 --> 00:04:42,675
If I take a little of the distance
and return to my earthly sphere,

45
00:04:42,675 --> 00:04:49,525
I will define a spherical
coordinate system...

46
00:05:01,327 --> 00:05:06,527
with the angular values relative to 
the reference planes. 

47
00:05:07,284 --> 00:05:14,464
So I summarize here: I have here my spherical 
coordinate system, 

48
00:05:14,464 --> 00:05:22,274
here my linear coordinate system,
and here my coordinate system

49
00:05:22,274 --> 00:05:23,724
on the plane.

50
