69
00:06:56,032 --> 00:06:57,802
The spherical coordinates. 

70
00:06:58,484 --> 00:07:00,694
Before defining spherical
coordinates, 

71
00:07:00,694 --> 00:07:05,194
we must characterize some
geometric quantities on Earth.

72
00:07:05,194 --> 00:07:09,744
The first thing that comes 
to mind is the axis of rotation...

73
00:07:11,589 --> 00:07:16,329
that cut the Earth 
at two characteristic points, 

74
00:07:16,329 --> 00:07:21,779
the north pole and south pole. 

75
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:28,760
Then, the reference plane, 
which is common knowledge, 

76
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:33,950
is the equator,
and in the other direction

77
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:37,950
we have the meridians 

78
00:07:38,692 --> 00:07:45,202
parallel to equator, 
we have planes called parallels. 

79
00:07:46,237 --> 00:07:50,527
With these geometric elements
we can now define

80
00:07:50,527 --> 00:07:53,247
a spherical coordinate system. 

81
00:07:53,529 --> 00:07:55,159
The spherical coordinates. 

82
00:07:55,159 --> 00:08:00,199
The first spherical coordinate, 
that interests us, is the latitude.

83
00:08:05,157 --> 00:08:12,367
Latitude is the angle
that is normal to the surface

84
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:16,367
with the plane of the equator. 

85
00:08:16,567 --> 00:08:29,017
It is the angle between the normal
of the surface and the equator. 

86
00:08:32,434 --> 00:08:39,504
The second spherical coordinate
is the longitude,...

87
00:08:41,809 --> 00:08:46,659
which is the angle between 
the meridian planes, 

88
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:55,429
the prime meridian, 
passing through Greenwich,

89
00:08:55,429 --> 00:08:59,429
and the meridian of a place considered.

90
00:08:59,807 --> 00:09:03,807
So we have this angle here between 
these two meridian planes. 

91
00:09:04,747 --> 00:09:09,667
In the figure, we see that, 
associated with these spherical coordinates, 

92
00:09:09,667 --> 00:09:16,857
we also have a frame here
Cartesian, geocentric, 

93
00:09:16,857 --> 00:09:21,897
with a z axis, which is the 
axis of rotation of Earth, 

94
00:09:21,897 --> 00:09:27,007
a x axis passing through the plane 
of the prime meridian

95
00:09:27,007 --> 00:09:32,877
and the equator, and a y axis,
which is perpendicular to the xy plane.

96
